      • compareTo

        public final int compareTo(Constraint c)
        Compare two constraints for orderedness. The function views each constraint as a triple (left, comp, right). The triples are compared lexicographically. Similarly, one element is less than another if and only if (1) the first is null and the second isn't, or (2) both are non-null and the hash code of the first is less than the hash code of the second.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Constraint>
        Parameters:
        c - the constraint to compare to
        Returns:
        -1 if this constraint is less than the other, +1 if it is greater, and 0 if they are equal
        See Also:
        Comparable.compareTo(java.lang.Object)
